{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=389146\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1322:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/factors-to-consider-for-creating-a-better-instagram-marketing-strategy/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/pexels-photo-248533.jpeg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"Factors To Consider For Creating A Better Instagram Marketing Strategy\" alt=\"Factors To Consider For Creating A Better Instagram Marketing Strategy\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">You may have come across people talking about Instagram marketing strategy but may not know how to go about it. Well, it needs a little effort and a strategic approach considering the different factors involved in it. If you give a little of your time you will be able to make the most of the [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/factors-to-consider-for-creating-a-better-instagram-marketing-strategy/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Walter Moore\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8064:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/factors-to-consider-for-creating-a-better-instagram-marketing-strategy/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/pexels-photo-248533.jpeg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"Factors To Consider For Creating A Better Instagram Marketing Strategy\" alt=\"Factors To Consider For Creating A Better Instagram Marketing Strategy\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>You may have come across people\ntalking about Instagram marketing strategy but may not know how to go about it.\nWell, it needs a little effort and a strategic approach considering the\ndifferent factors involved in it. If you give a little of your time you will be\nable to make the most of the 800 million active monthly users of this platform\nthat has more than 8 million business accounts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a mobile-based photo\nvideo-sharing social network platform that will allow you to reach to your targeted\ndemographics to engage them in a better way to drive more real social value as\nwell. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to studies, nearly\n60% of the <a href=\"https://gramista.com/\">Instagram followers</a> are young between the age group of 18 to 29 years. Therefore,\nInstagram is a highly competitive network through which you can reach out to this\nvaluable demographic. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Joining Instagram with their\ndigital marketing strategy, brands get a unique and enhanced opportunity to engage\nwith their fans in a better way. However, success for brands on Instagram needs\nmuch more than posting attractive images. You will need a:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Thoughtful strategy</li><li>Well-defined brand identity</li><li>Grounded visual creativity and </li><li>Effective community management. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You must also have a clear goal\nto achieve measurable results and follow a strategic and comprehensive guide.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You must focus on specific\nfeatures while <a href=\"https://www.quicksprout.com/2018/06/25/how-to-drive-sales-with-your-instagram-marketing-strategy/\">building\nyour Instagram marketing strategy</a> that includes:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Social media engagement </li><li>Instagram management</li><li>Instagram analytics</li><li>Audience targeting</li><li>Publishing calendar and</li><li>The objectives.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from these, you must also\nlook out for the best answers to a few specific questions such as:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>What do you want to achieve through Instagram? </li><li>What is the purpose of your brand for using\nInstagram? </li><li>What will Instagram allow you to do that the other\nplatforms will not?</li><li>Who is your target audience?</li><li>Which are the members of your audience that are most\nactive on Instagram?</li><li>How will Instagram integrate with the other social\nmedia networks in your marketing strategy?</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>It is only when you have your\nfocus and your objectives aligned, you will be able to showcase your culture, people,\nproducts and services through this unique platform.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Provides\nyou a better opportunity</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you use the mobile nature of\nInstagram perfectly for showing captured or in-the-moment pictures, you will\nget a better opportunity to give your Instagram followers a more personal scope\nto interact with your brand. It will also help you to engage in a way in which\nthe users will feel more casual, comfortable and instantaneous as compared with\nany other social media network.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on the type of\nbusiness you are involved with and the industry, you will have to consider the key\nperformance indicators according to your brand to make sure that your Instagram\nmarketing strategy is able to target your specific objectives that may include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Increasing brand awareness</li><li>Demonstrating company culture</li><li>Showcasing your team </li><li>Recruiting new talent</li><li>Increasing customer loyalty and engagement</li><li>Showcasing your products and services</li><li>Enhancing and complementing event experiences</li><li>Incentivizing consumer engagement</li><li>Sharing industry and company news</li><li>Building a more engaging community</li><li>Connecting with the influencers and </li><li>Driving sales through more organic traffic.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>When you create your Instagram\nmarketing strategy, these are the specific objectives that will guide you through\nthe process and help you to determine the best approach in each phase of the\nentire process. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Following\nthe best content strategy</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The primary requirement to make\nyour Instagram marketing strategy success is to develop ana better content strategy\nas this is the foundation of the entire process. A clearly defined and easy to\nunderstand content will determine your Instagram presence. There are several B2C\nbusinesses that use Instagram to make their product stand out and there are\nseveral other B2B companies on the other hand that often focus on team\nrecruitment and company culture. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, the best approach is to\nshow caseyour brand and develop a plan that is based on the objectives and\nneeds of the target audience. This will help you to deliver eye-catching\ncontent on a consistent basis to your community.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also have to follow a\nfew other steps to build a better and produce a highly effective Instagram\ncontent. One such is building proper <a href=\"http://chroniclerepublic.com/8-instagram-content-themes-to-boost-engagement/\">Instagram\ncontent themes</a>. For this, you will have to make sure that you:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Review your objectives</li><li>Determine the different aspects of your brand</li><li>Showcase the best content or pictures in your\nInstagram account</li><li>Consider posting pictures of your products,\nservices, company culture and your team members with proper balance</li><li>Offer rich potential for the subject matter over\ntime. </li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have a clear\nobjective, you must make a list of the specific content themes. You must then brainstorm\nall the possible subjects of your images and videos and make sure that you\nselect the ones that are perfectly suitable and relevant to your product or\nservices. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moreover, you must ensure that\nyour content themes align with your brand voice and are visually appealing as\nwell. For example, you can use similar visuals that will help you tell a better\nstory but make sure that these pictures are vibrant and colorful. The content must\nhighlight the product in such a way that it increases interaction through clicks\nand traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>To\nsum it up</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lots of studies and surveys\nhave found out that Instagram photos and videos with faces are very useful to generate\nlikes and comments. In fact, these pictures generate 38% more likes in\ncomparison to those that do not have any faces. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to build a proper\nand more effective Instagram marketing strategy you must make sure that you\nbuild your content themes considering what you know works well. The best way to\nensure this is by using the Instagram analytics tool. This will help you to benchmark\nyour content and at the same time, it will help you to see what the things are that\nactually drive engagement.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Do not start your market strategy building process without having the proper data. Always conduct a quick Instagram audit so that you will know about all those things that you need to know.<font color=\"#191e23\"><span><b> </b></span></font></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/factors-to-consider-for-creating-a-better-instagram-marketing-strategy/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/factors-to-consider-for-creating-a-better-instagram-marketing-strategy/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"How WordPress Helps to Make your Website GDPR Compliant\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-wordpress-helps-to-make-your-website-gdpr-compliant/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-wordpress-helps-to-make-your-website-gdpr-compliant/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 12 Mar 2019 17:18:57 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Introducing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=383396\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1268:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-wordpress-helps-to-make-your-website-gdpr-compliant/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/wordpress-and-gdpr.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"How WordPress Helps to Make your Website GDPR Compliant\" alt=\"How WordPress Helps to Make your Website GDPR Compliant\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">GDPR has been quite the buzz on the internet for some time now and has left several people scratching their heads not really knowing what it is and why is it crucial. This is especially true for website small website owners. The global reach of the GDPR has and the chances of potentially hefty fines [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-wordpress-helps-to-make-your-website-gdpr-compliant/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Safwana\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15818:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-wordpress-helps-to-make-your-website-gdpr-compliant/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/wordpress-and-gdpr.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"How WordPress Helps to Make your Website GDPR Compliant\" alt=\"How WordPress Helps to Make your Website GDPR Compliant\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>GDPR has been quite the buzz on the internet for some time now and has left several people scratching their heads not really knowing what it is and why is it crucial. This is especially true for website small website owners.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The global reach of the GDPR has and the chances of potentially hefty fines has prompted several websites to make the necessary changes in order to make their website GDPR compliant.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is GDPR and Why Should You Comply?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>GDPR or General Data Protection Regulation is a law that has come into effect on 25th May 2018. This law was designed for the sole purpose of protecting both the privacy and safety of European citizens. Even though the law aims to protect the privacy of only the citizens of the EU, an organization that has a user base in the EU has to comply with the law, regardless if they are based in the EU or not. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>GDPR came into effect replacing the Data Protection Directive 1995 to protect the data privacy of the citizens of the EU. The law was introduced to address how the user behavior and the data collection processes have changed and the need for better regulations to protect the privacy of the users<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>So, Why is GDPR important?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>GDPR had come into effect amidst news about data security breaches and misuse of user’s online data by many tech giants. People have been concerned about their privacy online. GDPR gives the users total control over their data.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>For businesses, an important reason to comply with the law is to secure the trust of the users. An organization that values and protects the privacy of it users is sure to gain the trust of its users which is pretty important for a business.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Does it Mean for Websites?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Different websites collect data from users in multiple ways and for multiple purposes. With GDPR, the website cannot collect information about the users as they did before. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is important to understand that the GDPR doesn’t prevent websites from using or collecting the data of website visitors. However, GDPR strictly advice websites to provide great control to users on how they use or collect their data. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before GDPR, the practice was to collect and process user data and their consent was not always informed and explicit.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, websites that collect or use any personal information of site visitors will have to obtain their explicit consent through a checkbox or other means. In addition to that, websites will have to provide details on how the personal information of site visitors will be used.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Where do Websites Start?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to ensure compliance is to understand the data collection process in the organization. Determine where the data are collected, how they are stored and processed, and what purposes they are stored for.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make a list of all the third-party services that are used on your website and for what purpose are they used. Determine the personal data that are collected by these services and how they are collected and processed. Information regarding such data collection should be provided to the users.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ensure that the data is stored in a secure manner. Put proper security measures, like encryption, in place to ensure that the data are stored in a secure manner. And implement proper mechanisms to inform the users if and when there is a data breach, as soon as possible.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The important aspect of the GDPR is the well informed consent of the users. So, whatever data that you are collecting, users should be well aware of it and they should give their explicit consent before the website can collect and use the data. The websites should make sure that they honor the rights of the users, which are the following:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The right to be informed</li><li>The right of access</li><li>The right to rectification</li><li>The right to erasure</li><li>The right to restrict processing</li><li>The right to data portability</li><li>The right to object to data processing</li><li>The rights in relation to automated decision making and profiling.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>GDPR can be hard to wrap your head around. In case you are struggling with the compliance, it is always recommended to hire a lawyer to guide you the right way.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What Steps Has WordPress Taken to Help Websites Comply with the Law?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are millions of websites that have been created using WordPress. So it is unavoidable that the popular CMS take steps to help website owners comply with the law.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress 4.9.6 is equipped with several handy built-in privacy settings. So, if you are using an outdated or older version of WordPress, you will need to upgrade to avail all these features. Some of the key features included in WordPress 4.9.6 that are useful for making your website GDPR compliant are discussed below.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Policy Generator</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The right to be informed is a key part of GDPR. This requires that the website have a privacy policy. Here, it is important to construct the privacy policy with simple and understandable language..<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you already have an existing privacy policy, you should consider updating it to meet the requirements of the law. With WordPress 4.9.6, you can designate a Privacy Policy page that will be displayed on the login and registration page.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, if you don’t have a privacy policy page, then you can also create one. To do that click on <strong>Settings</strong> followed by <strong>Privacy</strong> from you WordPress dashboard. Now, you will be able to see a <strong>Create New page</strong> option.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/privacy-settings-1024x533.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-383441\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/privacy-settings-1024x533.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/privacy-settings-300x156.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/privacy-settings-768x399.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/privacy-settings.png 1440w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Privacy Settings page in WordPress</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will generate a privacy policy page for you with suggestions for the privacy policy. It will make creating the privacy policy page easier, but it is the website owners responsibility to review and update according to their requirements.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Data Export and Erase</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress now makes it easier for website owners to honor user requests for access to their personal information and requests to delete their personal data.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this, you will be able to find two new features under the <strong>Tools</strong> option in the WordPress &#8211; &nbsp;<strong>Erase Personal data</strong> and <strong>Export Personal data</strong>. &nbsp;<br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/erase-personal-data-1-1024x476.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-383446\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/erase-personal-data-1-1024x476.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/erase-personal-data-1-300x140.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/erase-personal-data-1-768x357.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/erase-personal-data-1.png 1440w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Erase Personal Data page in WordPress<br></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As the name indicates, the Erase Personal Data option allows the website administrator to delete the personal data of a user easily. The admin can send an email confirming the request and then delete the user’s personal data. After deletion the user will be sent an email informing the same.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/export-personal-data-1024x476.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-383447\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/export-personal-data-1024x476.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/export-personal-data-300x140.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/export-personal-data-768x357.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/export-personal-data.png 1440w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Export Personal Data page in WordPress</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Export Personal Data option honors the request of the users to access the personal data that has been collected by the user. When the user places a request to access their data, the admin can send an email to confirm and then an email to download the data will be sent to the user.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, these options only helps in honoring these requests. The administrator has to implement a method with which the user can raise a request. For this, a contact form can be added on the website or any other details should be provided on the website for the users to raise such a request.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Comments Cookie Opt-in</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The WordPress stores personal data in cookies when a user enters a comment. This is done to help users from retyping their details when they are about to leave a new comment on websites. This was not done with the explicit consent of the user. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, WordPress allows to add an opt-in check box to the native comment box for the user when they are posting a comment. This can be be done checking the <strong>Show comments cookies opt-in checkbox </strong>options.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/comment-cookie-opt-in-1024x570.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-383448\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/comment-cookie-opt-in-1024x570.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/comment-cookie-opt-in-300x167.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/comment-cookie-opt-in-768x428.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/comment-cookie-opt-in.png 1440w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /><figcaption>Add cookie opt-in checkbox for comments</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>However, the check box might not appear depending on the theme being used. So you might have write additional CSS for that.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What are the Additional Steps Websites Should Take?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Although WordPress gives you all these features that will help you comply with the law, it does not make your website a 100% GDPR compliant. There are still many things that website need to take care of to comply with the law. For example, blocking cookies and data collection prior to user&#8217;s consent.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, what are the next steps that needs to be added to comply with the law?</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Update Privacy and Cookie Policies</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>WordPress now helps create a privacy policy easily. However, it can only be treated as a starting point. The privacy and cookie policies of a website varies a lot depending on the plugins and other third-party services uses.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The cookie policies must now be updated with all the cookies that are used on the website. The policies should now state why these cookies are used and how long they will be in use for. The policy should also provide information on how they can opt-out of the cookies. To know more about cookies, refer to <a href=\"https://cookielawinfo.com/what-are-cookies/\">this article</a>.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>A Cookie Notice Must Be Added</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You will need to provide information on the cookies that your website is using in order to make your website GDPR compliant. It is crucial to note that disclosing information about cookies should not just be restricted to your privacy policy. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cookies are installed by a website at the time of load. This means that you will need to inform the users about the cookies by adding a cookie notification at the same time when the user first visits. Fortunately, there are plenty of plugins that help you to do so and some of them are the following.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.webtoffee.com/product/gdpr-cookie-consent/\">GDPR Cookie Consent</a><strong>: </strong>The GDPR Cookie Consent plugin is an excellent plugin that can be used to ensure the GDPR compliance of your website. Location-based cookie notice exclusion, auto block scripts, and scanning websites for cookies are all possible with this plugin.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/cookie-notice/\">Cookie Notice</a><strong>: </strong>Cookie Notice is a free plugin that can be used to add an excellent cookie notification and opt-in to a website. The plugin also contains settings that will enable you to add a button to refuse or accept cookies, include a custom message, and even add links.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/gdpr-cookie-compliance/\">GDPR Cookie Compliance</a><strong>: </strong>The GDPR Cookie Compliance will help you with all your GDPR cookie consent compliance. The elegantly designed yet intuitive user interface and other handy features of this plugin is bound to impress you.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Policy Update and Data Breach Notifications</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Policy update and data breach notifications are another crucial part of GDPR compliance. These notifications are important for websites that provide user accounts, collect information of customers, and the ones with newsletters.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have already made changes to the privacy policy of your website in order to make it compliant with GDPR, then it is best to alert your site visitors about the changes. Most of the GDPR compliance WordPress plugins contains a built-in notification system, which will automatically send alerts to your site visitors.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>What are the Consequences of not Complying With GDPR?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Organizations that violate GDPR will have to pay hefty fines. The fines that can be imposed on an organization can be up to €20 million or 4% of the annual turnover of the previous financial year or whichever is higher.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>But it is important to note that this is the maximum of the fines that can be imposed on a website. Depending on the nature of infringement the supervisory authority can impose lesser fines or even take other actions like issuing a reprimand. Still, GDPR is not something to be taken lightly. If you are a small business and found not compliant, these fines could prove to be disastrous.<br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Disclaimer: This content should not be treated as legal advice and the article is not written by a lawyer. The website owners should seek legal advice if needed to know what is best for their website or app depending on which further actions may be required to fully comply with the law.</em><br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-wordpress-helps-to-make-your-website-gdpr-compliant/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-wordpress-helps-to-make-your-website-gdpr-compliant/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"Is Your WordPress Site Exposed to Attacks?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/is-your-wordpress-site-exposed-to-attacks/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/is-your-wordpress-site-exposed-to-attacks/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 07 Mar 2019 13:17:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Introducing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=374397\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1229:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/is-your-wordpress-site-exposed-to-attacks/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/computer-1591018_1920-2-1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"784\" title=\"Is Your WordPress Site Exposed to Attacks?\" alt=\"Is Your WordPress Site Exposed to Attacks?\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">You’ve put time and money into a brand new WordPress site. It has everything you wanted. Stunning graphics and visuals. Compelling content, sure to lure visitors and loyal customers. Maybe you’ve done the work yourself, or maybe you hired a pro to do it for you. Either way, the site is now in your hands [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/is-your-wordpress-site-exposed-to-attacks/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Alex\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6035:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/is-your-wordpress-site-exposed-to-attacks/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/computer-1591018_1920-2-1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"784\" title=\"Is Your WordPress Site Exposed to Attacks?\" alt=\"Is Your WordPress Site Exposed to Attacks?\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>You’ve put time and money into a brand new WordPress site. It has everything you wanted. Stunning graphics and visuals. Compelling content, sure to lure visitors and loyal customers. Maybe you’ve done the work yourself, or maybe you hired a pro to do it for you. Either way, the site is now in your hands to love and protect. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Protect? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Absolutely. According to Wordfence, a popular WordPress security plugin, Hackers launch attacks on WordPress sites over 90,978 times per minute. Considering those statistics, it’s imperative that your site is protected from attacks. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So what can you do to make sure you’ve created the strongest wall possible around your site? There are a number of ways. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But before we venture down that road, let&#8217;s talk about how you can initially set up and secure your site, and then check to see if it’s vulnerable to attacks. Knowing which holes to plug could be advantageous when you get to the next step of layering on protection. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Setting up a Secure Site</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Be wise when choosing a web host. There’s a reason why there’s such a range in hosting costs. If the server your site is hosted on is secure, that’s the first step in keeping your site safe. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Get your themes from reputable websites—like the WordPress site itself. Premium themes are beautiful and sometimes expensive. Don’t go looking for the cracked version because there&#8217;s a good chance you’ll end up with questionable code embedded in it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are a ton of good WordPress security plugins. Choose one that works for you and install it immediately. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Change the username from the default “admin” and choose a strong password. Those two things alone go a long way in protecting you. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Install an SSL Certificate. Frankly, everyone should have these on their sites now. Plenty of people have their browsers set to ignore sites without it. Why go to all the work of developing your site, only to make people afraid to visit. Quite a few hosts are offering them for free, so there’s really no excuse not to have one. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep your core WordPress up to date, along with all plugins and themes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Consider a VPN</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>VPNs, or Virtual Private Networks, aren’t infallible but they provide an excellent blanket protection to use as a base. Build upon that, and you’re nearly guaranteed a fully secure site. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the most part, your operating system shouldn’t matter when installing a VPN, but if you’re not a Windows user and you’re picky about your software, take a look at this information from VPN Pro, about well recognized <a href=\"http://vpnpro.com/vpn-reviews/nordvpn-review/\">NordVPN.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>A VPN will encrypt your information and let you access the internet from an anonymous IP address. Your data and the data of your customers is safe. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Scan your Site for Vulnerabilities</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you think you have everything set, make sure you’re good to go. There are services available online as well as plugins you can install that will scan your site. Depending on what you choose, they offer a variety of options. They may compare your site against a database that contains more than 4K WordPress weaknesses or vulnerabilities. Some will check for plugins and themes that haven’t been updated, which are often the source of known security holes that hackers are looking for. Some will check for spam that’s been injected in your code. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The above are just a few of the ways you can make sure your site is as secure as it can be. If you do detect weaknesses, here are a few ways to tighten your security. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Security Plugins </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>I mentioned the plugins above, but they deserve a bit more time. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several security plugins available, and a &nbsp;lot, if not most of them, have both free and premium versions. Should you buy the premium? Is that the only way to be sure you have the utmost protection on your site? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not necessarily. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Consider your site. Is it more of a hobby site that doesn’t run any eCommerce on it? Do you allow commenting? Basically, you’ll need to assess the level of protection you need. And even if you do have an eCommerce site, you may be okay with the basic security plugin, depending on what other measures you’ve taken to secure your site. &nbsp;There’s the list above of all the things a WordPress developer should do before they set their site free. Have you done that, and more? There’s a long list of manual things you can do to protect your site—more than we’ve mentioned here—so having done them may mean you can bypass the premium plugin. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>What about using a VPN? If you’ve added that layer to all the manual adjustments you can do to secure your site, again, there’s a good chance you don’t need to pay extra for a premium security plugin. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just another reason to use a VPN to protect your WordPress site. <br></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/is-your-wordpress-site-exposed-to-attacks/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/is-your-wordpress-site-exposed-to-attacks/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"How to boost your WooCommerce store results with OceanWP and Premmerce?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-boost-your-woocommerce-store-results-with-oceanwp-and-premmerce/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-boost-your-woocommerce-store-results-with-oceanwp-and-premmerce/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 06 Mar 2019 23:00:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Introducing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=380480\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1350:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-boost-your-woocommerce-store-results-with-oceanwp-and-premmerce/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/oceanwp_banner_2.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"How to boost your WooCommerce store results with OceanWP and Premmerce?\" alt=\"How to boost your WooCommerce store results with OceanWP and Premmerce?\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">Are you sure you’re making the most of your OceanWP theme? Premmerce is here to demonstrate how to amplify your users’ navigation and products presentation and as a result sell more with the help of its plugins. If you got interested, read on and learn about features we developed and integrated into the OceanWP theme [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-boost-your-woocommerce-store-results-with-oceanwp-and-premmerce/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"premmerce\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16812:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-boost-your-woocommerce-store-results-with-oceanwp-and-premmerce/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/oceanwp_banner_2.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"How to boost your WooCommerce store results with OceanWP and Premmerce?\" alt=\"How to boost your WooCommerce store results with OceanWP and Premmerce?\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>Are you sure you’re making the most of your OceanWP theme? Premmerce is here to demonstrate how to amplify your users’ navigation and products presentation and as a result sell more with the help of its plugins. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you got interested, read on and learn about features we developed and integrated into the OceanWP theme (which is one of the most popular themes in WordPress!). And, of course, we couldn&#8217;t but provide you with some real-life experience, so take your time and check out our OceanWP based <a href=\"http://oceanwp.premmerce.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">online store demo version here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Improving navigation features </h2>\n\n\n\n<h4>Premmerce WooCommerce Product Filter</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This plugin is a handy and flexible tool for managing filters for WooCommerce products. The main plugin features are a single widget that controls the display of all available filters and a well-designed caching system that improves the load speed, outperforming the standard WooCommerce filters.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Advanced SEO settings for filters and the ability to control the filter URLs formation are available in the Premium version of the plugin. You can learn about all the plugins features <a href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-product-filter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\" (opens in a new tab)\">here</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-1024x675.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380624\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-1024x675.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-300x198.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/1-768x506.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, you can view the OceanWP demo integrated with  Premmerce filters <a href=\"http://oceanwp.premmerce.com/clothes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Premmerce WooCommerce Variation Swatches</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Premmerce WooCommerce Variation Swatches will help you to visualize the product variations as well as enable your customers to buy a variational product from the product catalog.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can learn about all the plugin features <a href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-variation-swatches/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Display in the product archive:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-1024x657.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380723\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-1024x657.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-300x193.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2-768x493.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/2.png 1556w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Product variations are presented by colors and labels:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-1024x582.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380724\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-1024x582.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-300x171.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/3-768x437.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Product variations are presented by images:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/4-1024x563.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380725\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/4-1024x563.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/4-300x165.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/4-768x422.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also view the OceanWP demo with the Premmerce swatches set up  <a href=\"http://oceanwp.premmerce.com/clothes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Premmerce WooCommerce Product Search</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Premmerce Search turns ‘product search’ into a live search and also provides additional search results using spell correction.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can learn about all the plugin features <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-product-search/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/5-1024x474.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380729\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/5-1024x474.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/5-300x139.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/5-768x356.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also view the OceanWP demo with set up Premmerce search <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"http://oceanwp.premmerce.com\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Frequently Bought Together</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Premmerce Frequently Bought Together will help you to create product sets that will increase sales through discounts in a bundle. This is one of the main marketing tools used by Amazon to raise the average check. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You  can learn about all the plugin features <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-frequently-bought-together/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/6-1024x608.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380746\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/6-1024x608.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/6-300x178.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/6-768x456.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/6.png 1403w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Please view the OceanWP demo with Premmerce Frequently Bought Together <a href=\"http://oceanwp.premmerce.com/clothes/shirts/flowy-blouse/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tools for usability improvement</h2>\n\n\n\n<h4>Premmerce WooCommerce Wishlist</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>A wishlist is a tool that will allow your customers to choose and save products for future purchases and to share them with their friends. Just review wishlists and influence your customers’ by offering bargains and super deals based on the collected information.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can learn about all the plugin features <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-wishlist/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/7-1024x581.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380753\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/7-1024x581.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/7-300x170.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/7-768x435.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>Premmerce plugin addon &#8211; Premmerce Product Comparison</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Product comparison is a tool that will enable your customers to choose the best product, decide and make a purchase.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore the plugin features <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/premmerce-main-plugin-woocommerce-plugins-bundle/#reading-progress-title-4\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/8-1024x567.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380758\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/8-1024x567.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/8-300x166.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/8-768x425.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>Premmerce WooCommerce Brands</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>This plugin allows you to create an unlimited number of brands that can be assigned to products for better cataloging, product search and additional opportunities for marketing and product promotion by brands.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Discover all the plugin features <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/premmerce-woocommerce-brands-free-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/9-1-1024x606.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380764\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/9-1-1024x606.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/9-1-300x178.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/9-1-768x455.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also view the OceanWP demo with set up Premmerce brands <a href=\"http://oceanwp.premmerce.com/brands/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Premmerce Woocommerce Multi-currency</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Premmerce Woocommerce Multi-currency plugin allows you to start a multi-currency store with flexible settings and a number of additional unique features.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/10-1024x531.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380765\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/10-1024x531.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/10-300x156.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/10-768x398.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To display the currency switcher in the top bar, just add the [multicurrency] shortcode to the Content field in the theme Customizer:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/13-1024x581.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-381642\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/13-1024x581.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/13-300x170.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/13-768x436.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can learn about all the plugin features <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"here (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/premmerce-woocommerce-multi-currency/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Optimizing performance &#8211; Premmerce Performance Optimizer</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>WooCommerce often doesn’t handle a number of performance issues encountered by the stores with a large product base without cache and third-party optimization. Thus, we’ve studied this problem, and as a result, we’ve designed the plugin that automatically optimizes your online store operations.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, we’ve tested the performance of the OceanWP theme with 500k of products and the work of the Premmerce Performance Optimizer plugin. We’ve created the website where you can personally test and view all plugins in action.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The test results are shown in the diagram:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Test 1 &#8211; OceanWP + Premmerce  plugins</li><li>Test 2 &#8211; OceanWP + Premmerce plugins + Premmerce Performance Optimizer</li><li>Test 3 &#8211; OceanWP + Premmerce plugins + Premmerce Performance Optimizer + WP Rocket</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-1024x634.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380781\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-1024x634.png 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-300x186.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-768x475.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12.png 1380w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You can read more about the test results and plugin features on this <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"page (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-performance-optimizer/\" target=\"_blank\">page</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Additional plugins that don’t affect the store display</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also be interested in some  other Premmerce  plugins that will contribute to the flexible setup of your store:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Premmerce WooCommerce Permalink Manager (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-permalink-manager-remove-shop-product-product-category-url/\" target=\"_blank\">Premmerce WooCommerce Permalink Manager</a></strong> is developed to improve the current WooCommerce URL configuration features and provide your store with better display options and additional SEO capabilities to adhere to WooCommerce SEO Audit standards.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-redirect-manager/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Premmerce Redirect Manager (opens in a new tab)\">Premmerce Redirect Manager</a></strong> enables you to create 301 and 302 redirects and to set up the automatic redirects for the deleted products in the WooCommerce store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Premmerce User Roles (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://premmerce.com/wordpress-custom-user-roles/\" target=\"_blank\">Premmerce User Roles</a></strong> &#8211;  this plugin has been developed for creating user roles from the WordPress admin area and assigning the arbitrary access rights to them. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-customers-manager/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Premmerce WooCommerce Customers Manager (opens in a new tab)\">Premmerce WooCommerce Customers Manager</a></strong> extends the standard user list and the edit user page in WordPress and adds the customer data from WooCommerce. This is the main customer management plugin from Premmerce, which we constantly improve by adding new features, considering the needs of its users.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://premmerce.com/premmerce-woocommerce-wholesale-pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Premmerce Woocommerce Wholesale Pricing (opens in a new tab)\">Premmerce Woocommerce Wholesale Pricing</a></strong> allows you to add prices to products for each user roles.     </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://premmerce.com/woocommerce-seo-addon-yoast/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"WooCommerce SEO Addon (opens in a new tab)\">WooCommerce SEO Addon</a></strong> plugin extends the functionality of Yoast SEO for microdata management and provides all the instruments you need for your store’s SEO improvement.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Premmerce plugins pricing</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The free version is available in all Premmerce plugins and in many cases, it’s sufficient for dealing with a variety of issues. You can find all of them in the official <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/premmerce/#content-plugins\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"WordPress marketplace (opens in a new tab)\">WordPress marketplace</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some plugins offer Premium versions that complement and expand their basic capabilities. Also, the users of Premium versions get technical support and regular updates. Our team often add new features to the existing plugins, so your store is always trendy and functional as a result.  The price of Premium versions ranges from $ 45 to $ 65. Please, have a look at Premium versions in our marketplace.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Premmerce Suite</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to improve your OceanWP based online stores at once with all or most Premmerce plugins, we’ve prepared for you the <a href=\"https://premmerce.com/pricing/\">Premmerce Suite</a>, which provides the access to all the premium versions at a price just above the cost of 2 plugins.  Check it out!</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-boost-your-woocommerce-store-results-with-oceanwp-and-premmerce/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-boost-your-woocommerce-store-results-with-oceanwp-and-premmerce/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"7 Top Plugins to Turn a WordPress Site into a Mobile App\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/7-top-plugins-to-turn-a-wordpress-site-into-a-mobile-app/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/7-top-plugins-to-turn-a-wordpress-site-into-a-mobile-app/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 20 Feb 2019 18:20:39 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Introducing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=364764\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1307:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/7-top-plugins-to-turn-a-wordpress-site-into-a-mobile-app/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/wordpress-to-mobileapp.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"500\" title=\"7 Top Plugins to Turn a WordPress Site into a Mobile App\" alt=\"7 Top Plugins to Turn a WordPress Site into a Mobile App\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">Having a mobile app for your business has become inevitable if you want to be at the forefront of the competition. The reason is simple: a number of people are turning to their smartphones for almost everything &#8211; booking tickets, reading, shopping and much more. Earlier, mobile browsers or mobile websites were in the trend, [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/7-top-plugins-to-turn-a-wordpress-site-into-a-mobile-app/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Nirav Shastri\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12754:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/7-top-plugins-to-turn-a-wordpress-site-into-a-mobile-app/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/wordpress-to-mobileapp.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"500\" title=\"7 Top Plugins to Turn a WordPress Site into a Mobile App\" alt=\"7 Top Plugins to Turn a WordPress Site into a Mobile App\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>Having a mobile app for your business has become inevitable if you want to be at the forefront of the competition. The reason is simple: a number of people are turning to their smartphones for almost everything &#8211; booking tickets, reading, shopping and much more. Earlier, mobile browsers or mobile websites were in the trend, but today, it&#8217;s all about mobile apps. After all, they are convenient, fast and easy to use.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, are you planning to build a mobile app but worried about incurring the cost of the same?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, we have an amazing solution to it!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have already built a beautiful WordPress site, but not a mobile app, don&#8217;t worry. There&#8217;s always the much-in-trend DIY approach to opt for! Yes, even here!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With a WordPress plugin, you can create a new and all-mobile channel to be available to your target audience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are inquisitive to find more about how can a plugin assist in turning your WordPress site into a mobile app, take a look at the following!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Plugins that Can Convert a WordPress site into a mobile app</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the most popular plugins that can assist you in turning the WordPress site into a mobile app include:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1) <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/androapp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Androapp (opens in a new tab)\">Androapp</a> </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-364813\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1.jpg 750w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/1-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Opt for this plugin if you have a content-driven website like newspapers and blogs. This plugin takes your news feed and further turns it into a mobile-friendly layout. &nbsp;The outcome in the form of a mobile app will look similar to your responsive website. But, it obviously is more suitable than the website because of the presence of added functionalities like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Image zooming</li><li>Saving content offline</li><li>Send unlimited push notifications</li><li>In-line ads</li><li>Support for WordPress/Facebook comments</li><li>Support for deep linking (if you want to highlight different pages of your app in the search)</li><li>Infinite scroll facility</li><li>Custom theme and colors to match with your website</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>A quick note to follow here:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At least for time being, it is recommended to launch your app only on the Android platform as the functionality is currently in beta. But, building an iOS app can definitely be kept in your pipeline.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2) <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/apppresser/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"AppPresser (opens in a new tab)\">AppPresser</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-364814\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.jpg 750w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>AppPresser is quite easy to use and has a dedicated WordPress mobile theme that further creates the mobile app for your WordPress site. &nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you think that a free WordPress plugin won&#8217;t suffice your need and at the same time, don&#8217;t even want to pay for building the mobile app, this probably has to be your plugin choice. With it, you can get access to the following mobile app features:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>WordPress plugin and extension compatibility (this means you can integrate features like Google maps, Facebook login, camera connectivity and so on)</li><li>Design navigation as tabs or pull-out menu</li><li>Custom page creation</li><li>Push notification</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Though it brands to be easy in nature, it is not considered to be an ideal tool for the non-developers. It requires extensive customization to build your app from scratch and actually make it work as an app. So, consider this plugin if you have a developer&#8217;s assistance at your side.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3) <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/yournewsapp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Blappsta (opens in a new tab)\">Blappsta</a> </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-364815\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.jpg 750w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Blappsta is completely free to use and is compatible with both Android and iOS platforms. It comes with a unique feature of &#8216;Blappsta Preview&#8217; which lets you test and preview your experiments before actually making it live. So, you can see how your site will look like in the mobile app form even before creating it.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Its features include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Facility of push notifications when a new post is live</li><li>Deep linking indexing for Google</li><li>Facility of share buttons of various social media platforms like Facebook and Twitter</li><li>Flexibility in organizing the content on your mobile app</li><li>Customize navigation as well as home page design</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you create the mobile app, it can display popular articles, support the videos; display your Facebook page and much more. However, it is still relatively a new plugin compared to others.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4) <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/mobiloud-mobile-app-plugin/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"MobiLoud (opens in a new tab)\">MobiLoud</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-364816\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4.jpg 750w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/4-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Mobile App Canvas is a plugin created by MobiLoud which enables you to create a mobile app while launching it in both: Google Play Store and Apple App Store. It is one of the best plugin options to get a native mobile app from a WordPress site. You don&#8217;t need to create a separate theme, you can continue with your existing one for your app when you choose this plugin. Also, you have the flexibility of selecting a different theme altogether!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Features of MobiLoud include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Amazing range of themes for your mobile app</li><li>Customization of themes as per your preference with WordPress Customizer</li><li>Facility of adding a menu and animations to your mobile app</li><li>Automatic content updates</li><li>Push notification feature</li><li>Compatible on all major platforms &#8211; Android phone, iPhone, iPad and tablets</li><li>Mobile advertising and monetizing</li><li>Complete control over your app&#8217;s design and content</li><li>User-friendly</li><li>No technical knowledge required to create the app</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you download the Mobile App Canvas from MobiLoud, the team will take care of building the mobile app. Additionally, they will even maintain it. However, it&#8217;s not a free service. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5) <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/appful/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"appful (opens in a new tab)\">appful</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-364817\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5.jpg 750w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/5-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Being compatible with both: Android and iOS, appful is considered to be one of the best mobile app plugins to create a supreme mobile app. appful is created by SaaS company that assists companies, publishers and magazines to reach their target audience by creating enterprise software solutions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>appful provide features like:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Native social media sharing</li><li>offline reading</li><li>facility of &#8216;Read Later&#8217; and &#8216;Comments&#8217;</li><li>YouTube support</li><li>Live editing</li><li>Great app speed due to caching</li><li>Placing own advertisements in the app</li><li>Twitter profile page integration</li><li>Facility of using Google Analytics to inspect the mobile app traffic</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You are entitled with great mobile app designs at a fair price on appful which you can further customize them as per your preference. You will have to pay a nominal cost at the time of publishing your mobile app to the Apple App Store or Android Play Store. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>6) <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/web2application/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Web2App (opens in a new tab)\">Web2App</a> </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-364818\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6.jpg 750w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/6-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This WordPress plugin easily converts your responsive website into a full native app. Even if the setup is quite easy, you will not have to compromise on the quality of the mobile app if it is created with Web2App. It is both, suitable as well as an affordable choice of the plugin that serves you with different customization facilities.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the interesting mobile app features you can get with this plugin include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>App rating to get customer reviews on Google Play</li><li>Startup splash screen</li><li>Different ways for mobile app&#8217;s display and navigation</li><li>Social sharing</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Above all, they also provide you with a video tutorial so that you are able to create your mobile app easily with this plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>7) <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wapppress-builds-android-app-for-website/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"WappPress (opens in a new tab)\">WappPress</a></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-364819\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7.jpg 750w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/7-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>WappPress is considered to be the most cost-efficient platform while allowing you to convert WordPress website to Android app through simple click functionality. Here, you will not have to think of hiring the developers as even a non-developer can build the app with just a few settings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Features of using WappPress include:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Customizing features for templates and other pages</li><li>Multiple premade theme</li><li>Custom home page</li><li>Launcher icon</li><li>Custom splash screen</li><li>Push notifications</li><li>Google Play Store support</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have built your mobile app, you can simply publish it on Google&#8217;s Play Store on your own.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Which plugin will you choose?</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using any of these plugins to turn your WordPress site into a mobile app will carve your path towards reaching your target audience. Even if you have a responsive design, having a mobile app for your business will bring in more traffic, leads and ultimately sales.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, which plugin will you choose for your app? Are you aware of other plugins? Do tell us in the comments. </p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/7-top-plugins-to-turn-a-wordpress-site-into-a-mobile-app/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/7-top-plugins-to-turn-a-wordpress-site-into-a-mobile-app/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:25:\"https://oceanwp.org/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\